The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | AllBank forays into gold retail
                                                                                                               AllBank forays into gold retail
          A STAFF REPORTER                      AllBank chairman   K.R. Kamath in Calcutta  on Tuesday. Picture by   Kishor Roy Chowdhury                          
	Calcutta, April 14: City-based Allahabad Bank will sell gold coins and bars as part of its strategy to increase its fee-based income.        
	Allahabad Bank is the first bank from the eastern region to offer such a service.        
	The bank will sell gold bars and coins through select branches. Gold coins will be available in 4, 8 and 10 grams, and bars will be sold in 20 and 50 grams.         
	The bank has tied up with Produits Artistiques Metaux Precieux S.A. Geneva for the supply of gold.         
	The company supplies coins and bars to 17 banks in the country.        
	The gold coins will be Assay certified and will be competitively priced, Allahabad Bank chairman and managing director K.R. Kamath said. The bank had been importing gold for wholesale purposes till now.        
	Retailing will be done later in Maharashtra, south India and subsequently in the rest of the country.         
	The coins and bars will be priced on the basis of daily quotes in the international bullion market exclusive of VAT and sales tax.                                                                                                                                        
